---
import { withBase } from '../utils/paths';
import LegalLayout from '../components/legal/LegalLayout.astro';
import LegalSection from '../components/legal/LegalSection.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Draft Privacy Notice | BMR PrintCare"
  description="Preliminary privacy notice placeholder for BMR PrintCare, including local-first data direction and static website data collection status."
  eyebrow="Draft privacy notice"
  heading="Preliminary privacy notice for future review."
  intro="This draft explains the current privacy direction for the static website and the planned local-first desktop app while BMR PrintCare is still in development."
  currentPath="/privacy/"
>
  <LegalSection title="Current status">
    <p>
      BMR PrintCare is still in development, and the app is not publicly available yet. This privacy notice is a
      preliminary placeholder intended to guide future review before any public release, payment flow, analytics setup,
      newsletter, support intake, or account system is added.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Local-first data direction">
    <p>
      BMR PrintCare is designed with a local-first direction for desktop maintenance tracking. The intended product
      direction is that printer profiles, maintenance records, parts notes, reminders, and related app data are primarily
      managed on the user's own device rather than requiring a hosted account by default.
    </p>
    <p>
      Final technical details, storage behavior, backup options, export behavior, and any optional sync or support flows
      remain subject to implementation and legal review. Users should plan to maintain their own backups when the app is
      eventually released.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Website data collection status">
    <p>
      The current public website is a static Astro site. It does not include account registration, checkout, analytics,
      newsletter signup, contact forms, authentication, or backend data collection in the repository at this stage.
    </p>
    <p>
      Hosting providers, browsers, or network infrastructure may still process basic technical information such as IP
      addresses, request times, user agents, and security logs. A future production deployment should document the actual
      hosting provider and log retention details before launch.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="No compliance claim">
    <p>
      This draft does not claim that BMR PrintCare is compliant with LGPD, GDPR, CCPA, or any other privacy law. Future
      legal review should determine which laws apply, what disclosures are required, and whether additional privacy
      controls are needed before public availability.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Future changes">
    <p>
      If future milestones add analytics, crash reporting, support forms, email updates, licensing systems, payment
      processors, cloud features, or app distribution platforms, this notice should be updated before those features are
      launched. Related release status is listed on the <a href={withBase('/download/')}>release preparation page</a> and planned
      work is summarized on the <a href={withBase('/roadmap/')}>roadmap</a>.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>

  <LegalSection title="Support reference">
    <p>
      Until a final support channel is selected, privacy-related questions should be treated as part of the general
      product readiness work described in the <a href={withBase('/support/')}>support hub</a>. A reviewed contact method should be
      added before public launch.
    </p>
  </LegalSection>
</LegalLayout>
